          <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left">
<table cellpadding="2" width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0">
  
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">Designation: Torvill LM-8C &quot;Gekko&quot;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Easy to pilot, the Gekko is highly prized among Mech
    drivers. It's small size makes the Gekko much easier to control in uneven terrain and
    allows for a wider range of operational areas. Usually when working in conjunction with
    Badgers, the Gekko will patrol outlying areas.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/gekfrnt.JPG"><img SRC="images/Gekko/gekfrnt.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="Torvill LM-8C" width="200" height="150"></a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Part of the Gekko's success in rough terrain is the
    hip design. Similar to the Badger's, this is the original design that later had to be
    modified to support the weight of the Badger. In this configuration the Gekko has
    superior stability and taxes it's gyro system less. However the price for this mobility is
    lack of armor since to armor these joints would severly limit their range of motion.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/gekhip.JPG"><img SRC="images/Gekko/gekhip.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="The hip on the Gekko is dangerously exposed." width="200" height="150"></a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Armor is a serious issue throughout the leg assembly
    for the Gekko. As an ad hoc solution, crews have taken to attaching armor plate to the
    &quot;shin&quot; of the Gekko to provide at least partial protection. While the standard
    protection is proof against small arms and light artillery, the additional armor adds at
    least some measure of protection against larger caliber weapons and energy based guns
    also.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/geksd.JPG"><img SRC="images/Gekko/geksd.JPG" BORDER=0 ALT="The Gekko has light leg armor." width=200 height=150></a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>The Gekko has many firsts in it's design. Among
    these is the split toe. Offering greater stability and more terrain handling features than
    a solid toe the Gekko paved the way for other designs to begin incorporating the split
    toe. Additionally the foot has a hinged pivot to provide more clearance when swinging it
    forward to take a step.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/gkftbnt2.JPG"><img SRC="images/Gekko/gkftbnt2.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="A unique foot for the Gekko." width="200" height="150"></a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>When the Gekko design was first proposed, there was
    loud objection to placing such a large &quot;smartstick&quot; load in the missle pod.
    Individual cost, and the exposed position of the pod were part of the objections. The
    designers were unwilling to compromise, citing battlefield statistics and personal
    interviews with veterans. In the end, the misslepod and it's 200 &quot;smartstick&quot;
    load have been major contributions to the effectiveness of the Gekko. Providing a
    &quot;fire and forget&quot; capability, the Gekko can engage multiple targets at long
    ranges.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/gekpod.JPG"><img SRC="images/Gekko/gekpod.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="200 smartstick missle pod." width="200" height="150"></a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>To give the Gekko a balanced weapons load out, two
    PAcs were fitted to the port weapons mount with two light lasers sandwiched. The PAcs
    aren't as powerful as the Vericoil guns of the Badger, but running off the Gekko's fusion
    bottle, still have about half the penetration power. The PAcs are intended mostly as light
    Mech, and heavy tracked armor weapons. For lighter units the twin lasers may be used at a
    much smaller energy cost.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/gekgun.JPG"><img SRC="images/Gekko/gekgun.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="Twin PAcs, twin lasers." width="200" height="150"></a></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Another technology first used on the Gekko is the
    signature reduction gear. Primarily a noise, exhaust and heat scrubber, the gear sits atop
    the main exhaust vent from the Gekko's fusion bottle generator. As also evidenced in
    Badger camps the screened emissions that are released are mostly carbon dioxide and water,
    contributing to significant plant growth around long term Gekko staging locations. Plans
    for the Gekko are in production according to the Commandant as well as for the Badger.</td>
    <td><a HREF="images/Gekko/gekeng.jpg"><img SRC="images/Gekko/gekeng.jpg" BORDER="0" ALT="A single engine silencer for the Gekko." width="200" height="150"></a></td>
  </tr>
</table>
